1
00:00:00,933 --> 00:00:01,633
<i>I already told Martin
that Uncle Ronald</i>

2
00:00:01,767 --> 00:00:02,767
<i> will be our partner.</i>

3
00:00:02,900 --> 00:00:04,733
<i>Did you fall for
your friend's tricks, Leon?</i>

4
00:00:04,833 --> 00:00:08,033
When I say it's not Uncle Andy,
<i> it's not Uncle Andy!</i>

5
00:00:08,333 --> 00:00:10,433
<i>They don't just want
to be part of the hotel,</i>

6
00:00:10,600 --> 00:00:12,767
<i>they want to see or get
something from me.</i>

7
00:00:12,933 --> 00:00:15,300
<i> It must be something valuable.</i>

8
00:00:15,467 --> 00:00:16,933
<i>He said we
shouldn't sell the hotel</i>

9
00:00:17,100 --> 00:00:18,533
<i>because there's
something important.</i>

10
00:00:18,633 --> 00:00:20,600
<i>It looks like Sir Ronald
has a problem.</i>

11
00:00:20,733 --> 00:00:21,900
<i>He already found out
the truth,</i>

12
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:23,433
that Sari isn't your girlfriend.

13
00:00:23,600 --> 00:00:24,933
<i>You were raised
by a businessman.</i>

14
00:00:25,100 --> 00:00:28,067
<i>I'm disappointed
that you don't value</i>

15
00:00:28,167 --> 00:00:30,767
<i>the character of the people
around you.</i>

16
00:00:33,800 --> 00:00:35,367
<i>It looks like he's learning
a lot already.</i>

17
00:00:35,500 --> 00:00:37,000
<i>So I need you to find
something you can use</i>

18
00:00:37,133 --> 00:00:38,267
<i> against the Almazans.</i>

19
00:00:38,433 --> 00:00:41,900
<i>And not just them,
but also Fernandez's children.</i>

20
00:00:47,633 --> 00:00:48,600
So...

21
00:00:48,767 --> 00:00:49,800
Did you find anything?

22
00:00:51,500 --> 00:00:53,300
What exactly are we looking for?

23
00:00:54,133 --> 00:00:56,233
Something important to Papa.

24
00:00:56,933 --> 00:00:58,600
[MONETTE] Oh, there!

25
00:00:58,767 --> 00:01:00,600
[MOUTH CLICKS]
I got it, I got it, I got it.

26
00:01:01,533 --> 00:01:03,300
I found it!

27
00:01:04,267 --> 00:01:06,600
Your siblings aren't here
right now.

28
00:01:06,800 --> 00:01:08,267
So I'll touch them too.

29
00:01:08,833 --> 00:01:10,433
[MOUTH CLICKS] Monette...

30
00:01:11,700 --> 00:01:12,833
I'm touched.

31
00:01:13,700 --> 00:01:15,867
But we're not the ones
Papa was referring to.

32
00:01:16,700 --> 00:01:17,767
[SIGHS]

33
00:01:17,867 --> 00:01:24,700
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

34
00:01:24,833 --> 00:01:31,700
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

35
00:02:25,100 --> 00:02:26,500
Isn't there any other clue?

36
00:02:27,100 --> 00:02:28,000
Is it a person?

37
00:02:28,467 --> 00:02:30,033
One word? Tagalog?

38
00:02:30,200 --> 00:02:31,100
How many syllables?

39
00:02:31,233 --> 00:02:32,500
What does it sound like?

40
00:02:33,367 --> 00:02:34,667
[MONETTE] You turned
this into charades.

41
00:02:34,800 --> 00:02:35,733
Come on!

42
00:02:36,800 --> 00:02:38,933
This is because
of team building.

43
00:02:39,067 --> 00:02:40,700
I'm entering my gaming era.

44
00:02:41,733 --> 00:02:42,833
Raphie.

45
00:02:43,367 --> 00:02:45,333
It's a document or a file.

46
00:02:45,467 --> 00:02:49,367
Oh! What we're looking for
is actually so easy.

47
00:02:50,167 --> 00:02:51,633
Raphie, be serious for a second.

48
00:02:53,400 --> 00:02:54,700
That was fast.

49
00:02:56,067 --> 00:02:57,400
Sorry about that.

50
00:02:58,333 --> 00:02:59,600
We just thought that...

51
00:02:59,733 --> 00:03:01,600
you've been with Papa
the longest.

52
00:03:01,733 --> 00:03:04,533
So you'd know better
what matters to him.

53
00:03:05,567 --> 00:03:08,367
Hey, we're not complaining.

54
00:03:08,967 --> 00:03:11,700
We just really want
to speed up our search.

55
00:03:11,800 --> 00:03:12,700
[RAPHIE] Yeah.

56
00:03:12,833 --> 00:03:15,267
And we were just
messing around earlier.

57
00:03:15,400 --> 00:03:16,467
[MONETTE] Yeah.

58
00:03:17,067 --> 00:03:18,800
I'm just worried.

59
00:03:20,100 --> 00:03:21,733
Martin started this.

60
00:03:21,933 --> 00:03:24,167
And there are things
he's not telling us.

61
00:03:24,300 --> 00:03:25,300
[MONETTE SIGHS DEEPLY]

62
00:03:25,433 --> 00:03:27,600
The Martin I know...

63
00:03:27,767 --> 00:03:29,733
he's the type of person
who won't ask for help

64
00:03:29,833 --> 00:03:31,333
as long as he can
handle it alone.

65
00:03:31,467 --> 00:03:35,067
That means it's really
important.

66
00:03:35,500 --> 00:03:36,933
[RAPHIE SIGHS]

67
00:03:38,300 --> 00:03:39,433
- [RAPHIE EXHALES]
- Oh?

68
00:03:39,600 --> 00:03:41,267
What is this, sis?
Giving up?

69
00:03:41,433 --> 00:03:42,900
[RAPHIE] Shh!

70
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:47,433
They say, when you're not
looking for something,

71
00:03:47,600 --> 00:03:49,100
that's when it appears.

72
00:03:49,833 --> 00:03:52,000
So let's stop looking for it
so it comes to us.

73
00:03:53,167 --> 00:03:55,267
[INHALES, EXHALES]

74
00:03:55,467 --> 00:03:57,100
Come on, universe!

75
00:03:57,633 --> 00:03:59,433
Come on, destiny... [EXHALES]

76
00:04:00,067 --> 00:04:01,933
Show what's meant to be.

77
00:04:03,167 --> 00:04:04,500
Thank you.

78
00:04:06,700 --> 00:04:08,267
Uh, Jade.

79
00:04:08,367 --> 00:04:12,367
You know our coffee updates
aren't required anymore, right?

80
00:04:15,400 --> 00:04:16,633
- But since the--
- Edward.

81
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:19,333
[CHUCKLES AWKWARDLY]

82
00:04:19,867 --> 00:04:21,500
Okay, sure.

83
00:04:21,633 --> 00:04:23,933
You go first.
What were you going to say?

84
00:04:26,667 --> 00:04:29,600
Since the point of our
coffee update is to share,

85
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:34,633
I want to formally tell you
that I'm going to court you.

86
00:04:36,267 --> 00:04:37,467
[HUFFS]

87
00:04:38,067 --> 00:04:40,733
E-Edward, you've already
told me that, right?

88
00:04:41,533 --> 00:04:42,867
What I mean is...

89
00:04:43,733 --> 00:04:46,633
I want to formally tell
your family

90
00:04:47,400 --> 00:04:49,033
that I'm going to court you.

91
00:04:51,333 --> 00:04:54,167
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

92
00:04:54,333 --> 00:04:55,533
I...

93
00:04:57,533 --> 00:04:59,733
I don't think
this is the right time.

94
00:05:01,533 --> 00:05:05,867
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

95
00:05:06,033 --> 00:05:07,000
Why?

96
00:05:08,867 --> 00:05:09,900
Why?

97
00:05:12,600 --> 00:05:14,000
Because of your dad.

98
00:05:15,300 --> 00:05:16,400
My dad?

99
00:05:16,533 --> 00:05:21,867
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

100
00:05:22,033 --> 00:05:24,867
Edward, do you know
what Uncle Andy did

101
00:05:25,033 --> 00:05:28,167
that made Leon refuse
to be his business partner

102
00:05:28,300 --> 00:05:29,833
here at the hotel?

103
00:05:33,033 --> 00:05:34,200
What my dad did?

104
00:05:34,400 --> 00:05:35,933
What did my dad do?

105
00:05:38,467 --> 00:05:41,133
Did Leon and Uncle Andy
have a fight?

106
00:05:42,233 --> 00:05:43,767
Did they fight--

107
00:05:44,733 --> 00:05:47,200
[STAMMERS] Did Uncle Andy
have a failed business venture

108
00:05:47,300 --> 00:05:48,700
that my brother found out about?

109
00:05:50,467 --> 00:05:51,933
Nothing.

110
00:05:52,600 --> 00:05:55,700
I mean, all of our businesses
are doing fine.

111
00:05:56,567 --> 00:05:58,033
And as far as I know...

112
00:05:59,567 --> 00:06:01,233
he and Leon are okay.

113
00:06:01,567 --> 00:06:03,400
Then there must be something.

114
00:06:04,467 --> 00:06:06,433
If there's a problem like this,
Edward,

115
00:06:06,567 --> 00:06:08,900
Leon's judgment of you
might change.

116
00:06:09,100 --> 00:06:15,900
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

117
00:06:18,933 --> 00:06:20,567
Did you come from Sir Ronald?

118
00:06:20,667 --> 00:06:21,900
What did he say?

119
00:06:26,767 --> 00:06:27,467
Okay.

120
00:06:27,600 --> 00:06:29,633
That doesn't look okay.

121
00:06:32,767 --> 00:06:34,067
This is the contract
I'm supposed to have

122
00:06:34,167 --> 00:06:35,233
Uncle Andy sign.

123
00:06:40,133 --> 00:06:41,233
Read it first.

124
00:06:42,400 --> 00:06:45,433
- [MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]
- [PAPER RIPS]

125
00:06:45,567 --> 00:06:46,467
[PAPER SLAPPED DOWN]

126
00:06:46,633 --> 00:06:47,800
- [LUNA SNICKERS]
- No.

127
00:06:48,200 --> 00:06:49,267
[SCOFFS]

128
00:06:49,400 --> 00:06:51,000
You know,
I can print another one.

129
00:06:52,633 --> 00:06:55,700
And I'll keep tearing those
contracts again and again

130
00:06:55,833 --> 00:06:58,267
until you understand
that no matter what,

131
00:06:58,367 --> 00:07:00,767
Andy Arellano will never be
a partner of this hotel!

132
00:07:00,900 --> 00:07:03,200
Why do you hate
Uncle Andy so much?!

133
00:07:03,333 --> 00:07:04,600
I just do!

134
00:07:05,200 --> 00:07:06,367
That's not a valid reason!

135
00:07:06,500 --> 00:07:08,100
Your brother
doesn't like him either!

136
00:07:08,233 --> 00:07:09,600
That's your brother!

137
00:07:10,867 --> 00:07:12,667
I won't stop until I find out

138
00:07:12,800 --> 00:07:15,000
why you both don't like
Uncle Andy.

139
00:07:15,833 --> 00:07:16,567
Leon.

140
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:19,900
Jade, if this is about
Uncle Andy...

141
00:07:20,033 --> 00:07:21,167
Leon, please...

142
00:07:21,333 --> 00:07:23,300
I just want to understand.

143
00:07:26,400 --> 00:07:29,567
There are business decisions
that I don't explain to you.

144
00:07:29,700 --> 00:07:32,233
But, Leon,
this directly involves me.

145
00:07:32,367 --> 00:07:34,133
This isn't just about
Uncle Andy.

146
00:07:34,267 --> 00:07:35,567
It's also about Edward.

147
00:07:36,333 --> 00:07:37,967
[RAPHIE] Sir! Sir, Leon!

148
00:07:38,067 --> 00:07:38,800
Raphie, what is it?

149
00:07:38,900 --> 00:07:41,033
Sir, Sir Martin and Ma'am Luna--

150
00:07:41,167 --> 00:07:42,000
What happened?

151
00:07:42,167 --> 00:07:43,033
[RAPHIE] They're arguing.

152
00:07:43,167 --> 00:07:44,033
- What?!
- What?!

153
00:07:44,167 --> 00:07:45,533
Y-yes, it's getting worse.

154
00:07:45,667 --> 00:07:46,833
- They're over there by the--
- [PANTING]

155
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:48,300
[JADE] Thank you, Raphie.
Come on.

156
00:07:48,467 --> 00:07:49,567
[MARTIN]
Now I'm the selfish one?!

157
00:07:49,700 --> 00:07:51,167
Because you're doing
whatever you want

158
00:07:51,267 --> 00:07:52,167
without any explanation!

159
00:07:52,367 --> 00:07:55,533
Leon and I already said
he is the better choice!

160
00:07:55,700 --> 00:07:57,400
Isn't that explanation enough?

161
00:07:57,533 --> 00:07:58,567
Better choice?!

162
00:07:58,700 --> 00:08:01,100
How is he the better choice
if he backed out?

163
00:08:01,900 --> 00:08:03,033
[MARTIN] You know that?

164
00:08:03,200 --> 00:08:10,000
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

165
00:08:18,300 --> 00:08:19,700
Did you tell her?

166
00:08:19,867 --> 00:08:20,900
So you're on the same side now?!

167
00:08:21,067 --> 00:08:22,933
Because we both have doubts
about you and Leon!

168
00:08:23,067 --> 00:08:24,533
You want us to trust
that decision,

169
00:08:24,667 --> 00:08:26,467
but you're not telling us
the truth!

170
00:08:26,600 --> 00:08:30,200
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

171
00:08:30,333 --> 00:08:31,700
There!

172
00:08:34,733 --> 00:08:36,300
Leon, what did you tell Martin?

173
00:08:42,900 --> 00:08:44,933
Ever since you came back
and talked to Martin,

174
00:08:45,067 --> 00:08:47,200
he's been more firm
about choosing Sir Ronald!

175
00:08:50,333 --> 00:08:51,467
What did you tell him?!

176
00:08:51,600 --> 00:08:57,033
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

177
00:08:57,167 --> 00:08:58,067
What?!

178
00:08:59,333 --> 00:09:00,767
Say something!

179
00:09:03,300 --> 00:09:05,733
In case you forgot, seven of us
who own this hotel,

180
00:09:05,867 --> 00:09:07,500
so it can't just be
the two of you who know!

181
00:09:07,633 --> 00:09:14,667
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

182
00:09:28,067 --> 00:09:31,300
[CLUB MUSIC PLAYING
IN BACKGROUND]

183
00:09:31,300 --> 00:09:34,467
Are you guys sure you want
me to keep this map?

184
00:09:34,467 --> 00:09:35,500
Yes.

185
00:09:35,833 --> 00:09:38,400
There's a lot going on
in our house right now,

186
00:09:38,400 --> 00:09:40,000
so it'll be hard for me
to keep that.

187
00:09:41,033 --> 00:09:42,533
Justin is right.

188
00:09:42,533 --> 00:09:44,500
Besides, you're more careful.

189
00:09:47,567 --> 00:09:49,300
Sorry. No offense.

190
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:54,533
Okay then, if that's what
you want.

191
00:09:54,533 --> 00:09:55,833
[PHONE CHIMES]

192
00:09:55,833 --> 00:10:01,367
[CLUB MUSIC CONTINUES
PLAYING IN BACKGROUND]

193
00:10:01,400 --> 00:10:02,533
What?!

194
00:10:02,533 --> 00:10:04,067
- Oops! Ow!
- Hey.

195
00:10:04,067 --> 00:10:08,500
[CLUB MUSIC CONTINUES
PLAYING IN BACKGROUND]

196
00:10:08,500 --> 00:10:10,400
Be careful.

197
00:10:10,400 --> 00:10:11,600
This chair is high,
remember?

198
00:10:11,600 --> 00:10:13,567
It's not that. I'm fine.

199
00:10:13,567 --> 00:10:14,900
Raphie sent me a text
message.

200
00:10:15,933 --> 00:10:17,233
[RAPHIE] Come home now.

201
00:10:17,233 --> 00:10:20,567
<i> Miss Luna and Sir Martin
are fighting again.</i>

202
00:10:20,567 --> 00:10:23,067
- [UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]
- Shoot! I have to go!

203
00:10:23,067 --> 00:10:25,300
- Take care.
- Wait, where are you going?

204
00:10:26,867 --> 00:10:29,000
- He's going to the hotel.
- Why?

205
00:10:29,000 --> 00:10:31,367
His sister, Luna,
got into a conflict.

206
00:10:31,367 --> 00:10:32,700
What?

207
00:10:34,567 --> 00:10:37,533
He really couldn't stop being
worried for his family.

208
00:10:38,800 --> 00:10:40,433
Yeah.

209
00:10:40,433 --> 00:10:43,367
Justin may seem like
he doesn't care,

210
00:10:43,367 --> 00:10:48,333
but he'd do anything
for his family.

211
00:10:51,100 --> 00:10:52,733
Yeah, that's true.

212
00:10:54,733 --> 00:10:58,033
Oh! Sorry, Trixie. It's Martin
and Luna who are fighting.

213
00:10:58,767 --> 00:10:59,800
Sorry, sorry, sorry.

214
00:10:59,800 --> 00:11:01,433
My goodness, Cheska.
Why didn't you tell me?

215
00:11:01,433 --> 00:11:03,900
- Come on, let's go.
- Alright.

216
00:11:05,300 --> 00:11:06,400
Well?

217
00:11:07,400 --> 00:11:08,933
You're both not going
to talk?

218
00:11:08,967 --> 00:11:15,567
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

219
00:11:15,567 --> 00:11:16,767
[KIKO] Martin.

220
00:11:19,233 --> 00:11:20,700
Leon, what's that about?

221
00:11:21,967 --> 00:11:23,700
Tell me what's going on!

222
00:11:26,667 --> 00:11:28,367
[GIO] So this is how
it's going to be, huh?

223
00:11:29,600 --> 00:11:31,900
Don't you care about
your siblings?!

224
00:11:31,900 --> 00:11:38,633
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

225
00:11:38,633 --> 00:11:40,933
Uncle Andy won't be
good for the hotel.

226
00:11:40,933 --> 00:11:41,967
That's it!

227
00:11:43,267 --> 00:11:46,033
You are being unreasonable,
Leon.

228
00:11:46,033 --> 00:11:48,000
This isn't just about you!

229
00:11:50,433 --> 00:11:51,433
[KIKO] Jade!

230
00:11:52,367 --> 00:11:59,267
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

231
00:12:04,333 --> 00:12:05,300
[GLASS THUDS]

232
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:14,900
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

233
00:12:17,700 --> 00:12:23,700
- [BIRDS CHIRPING IN DISTANCE]
- [BREATHING HEAVILY]

234
00:12:23,700 --> 00:12:24,767
[DOOR OPENS]

235
00:12:26,700 --> 00:12:29,033
What did you do to the
Almazans, Dad?

236
00:12:29,200 --> 00:12:30,367
What?

237
00:12:31,133 --> 00:12:33,367
What did you do to them?

238
00:12:35,233 --> 00:12:38,633
Can you at least let me inside
my house first

239
00:12:38,633 --> 00:12:40,767
before you ask me
questions?

240
00:12:42,033 --> 00:12:43,533
[GRUNTS]

241
00:12:45,667 --> 00:12:48,600
To answer your question,
I didn't do anything wrong.

242
00:12:49,767 --> 00:12:52,700
So, why is Leon against
us being partners of Hotel 88?

243
00:12:52,700 --> 00:12:53,967
I don't know.

244
00:12:54,167 --> 00:12:55,833
Why don't you ask him?

245
00:12:55,833 --> 00:12:57,000
Dad.

246
00:12:57,000 --> 00:12:59,433
Would you listen
to yourself, bud?

247
00:12:59,433 --> 00:13:00,667
They're the ones
who refused

248
00:13:00,667 --> 00:13:02,867
even though I'm not
doing anything wrong.

249
00:13:02,867 --> 00:13:05,933
Don't make me turn out to
be the bad guy here, okay?

250
00:13:05,933 --> 00:13:07,033
It's me.

251
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:11,500
[EDWARD SIGHS]

252
00:13:11,500 --> 00:13:18,467
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

253
00:13:21,033 --> 00:13:23,433
It's just that I talked
to Jade

254
00:13:23,467 --> 00:13:25,367
about the partnership.

255
00:13:26,567 --> 00:13:29,833
Leon's judgment could affect
what she thinks of me.

256
00:13:30,467 --> 00:13:32,867
- So?
- "So?"

257
00:13:32,867 --> 00:13:35,433
Jade values the opinion
of her siblings.

258
00:13:36,733 --> 00:13:38,067
[SIGHS SHARPLY]

259
00:13:39,067 --> 00:13:41,700
I thought you said you weren't
serious about Jade.

260
00:13:46,533 --> 00:13:48,767
And now you're acting like
that because of her?

261
00:13:56,467 --> 00:13:57,533
[KIKO] Jade!

262
00:13:58,733 --> 00:14:00,533
Jade, it's dangerous here.

263
00:14:01,733 --> 00:14:02,700
Jade!

264
00:14:04,733 --> 00:14:06,100
Let's go back, please!

265
00:14:06,100 --> 00:14:10,900
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

266
00:14:10,900 --> 00:14:12,533
Jade.

267
00:14:15,633 --> 00:14:22,667
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

268
00:14:22,667 --> 00:14:24,700
- Aah!
- Jade, what's wrong?!

269
00:14:25,900 --> 00:14:27,633
[KIKO GASPS, PANTS]

270
00:14:28,667 --> 00:14:29,767
Jade.

271
00:14:31,133 --> 00:14:34,100
He's dead!
Kiko, there's a dead body!

272
00:14:34,100 --> 00:14:35,800
There's a dead body!

273
00:14:35,800 --> 00:14:36,867
[JADE BREATHING SHAKILY]

274
00:14:36,867 --> 00:14:39,200
Oh my-- Oh my god!
Oh my god!

275
00:14:39,200 --> 00:14:41,500
[JADE BREATHING HEAVILY]

276
00:14:41,500 --> 00:14:42,900
Kiko.

277
00:14:44,467 --> 00:14:46,500
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

278
00:14:49,667 --> 00:14:56,500
- [DARK MUSIC PLAYING]
- [CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING]

279
00:15:03,633 --> 00:15:04,933
Syvera.

280
00:15:05,067 --> 00:15:11,267
- [DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING]

281
00:15:12,700 --> 00:15:14,467
Can you identify him?

282
00:15:14,633 --> 00:15:20,833
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

283
00:15:22,067 --> 00:15:24,600
Yes. Peter Montevilla.

284
00:15:26,400 --> 00:15:27,467
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

285
00:15:27,633 --> 00:15:29,200
His name is Peter Montevilla.

286
00:15:33,800 --> 00:15:34,967
He's the one who
caused the trouble.

287
00:15:35,167 --> 00:15:37,733
He's the one we
asked you to find.

288
00:15:37,867 --> 00:15:44,033
- [CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING]
- [SORROWFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

289
00:15:44,167 --> 00:15:50,033
[SOBBING]

290
00:15:51,600 --> 00:15:55,567
[SNIFFLING]

291
00:15:55,700 --> 00:16:02,633
[SORROWFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

292
00:16:16,033 --> 00:16:18,500
I know you are all worried
about what happened.

293
00:16:18,600 --> 00:16:21,567
I just want to tell you
that you guys are safe.

294
00:16:21,700 --> 00:16:23,767
Your safety is our
top priority,

295
00:16:23,933 --> 00:16:26,600
so we have already
added more security.

296
00:16:26,767 --> 00:16:29,767
Sir Martin, what most of us
are thinking right now is,

297
00:16:29,933 --> 00:16:33,767
will this have a big effect
on our jobs?

298
00:16:33,933 --> 00:16:36,400
Will Hotel 88
close down again, sir?

299
00:16:36,567 --> 00:16:39,200
The death didn't happen
inside the hotel, so...

300
00:16:39,300 --> 00:16:41,500
it probably won't affect us.

301
00:16:41,600 --> 00:16:44,533
But they were checking out
earlier, sir.

302
00:16:44,667 --> 00:16:46,900
If I were them, I'd
probably do the same.

303
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:49,100
But let's just give it
a few days,

304
00:16:49,233 --> 00:16:52,733
the fear will fade once
they know the truth...

305
00:16:52,833 --> 00:16:54,900
That it is safe here
in our hotel.

306
00:16:57,300 --> 00:16:59,267
We are going to
need your help.

307
00:17:00,233 --> 00:17:03,933
We need to show arriving
guests that they are all safe.

308
00:17:04,967 --> 00:17:07,133
That's all.
Thank you, everyone.

309
00:17:07,300 --> 00:17:09,433
And in the meantime,
I will be handling concerns

310
00:17:09,600 --> 00:17:12,067
while our general manager
is on leave.

311
00:17:12,167 --> 00:17:13,800
Yes, sir.

312
00:17:13,933 --> 00:17:15,100
Thank you.

313
00:17:15,300 --> 00:17:22,100
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

314
00:17:22,200 --> 00:17:23,500
I'll just go to Luna.

315
00:17:23,667 --> 00:17:30,633
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

316
00:17:31,700 --> 00:17:34,733
The partner issue isn't even
over, and now we have this.

317
00:17:37,633 --> 00:17:40,633
Sir Ronald will surely
hear about this.

318
00:17:41,033 --> 00:17:42,633
Will you be able
to convince him?

319
00:17:42,800 --> 00:17:48,400
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES,
THEN FADES]

320
00:17:52,633 --> 00:17:53,933
Ma'am?

321
00:17:54,033 --> 00:17:55,133
This is ready.

322
00:17:55,233 --> 00:17:57,633
Just move it to a bowl
while it's hot, okay?

323
00:17:57,733 --> 00:18:00,467
Then, uh...
no more apples, okay? Um...

324
00:18:00,567 --> 00:18:02,967
Just bananas so it's
easier for Luna to eat.

325
00:18:03,067 --> 00:18:04,200
Thank you.

326
00:18:07,300 --> 00:18:09,133
Oh. Justin, how's Luna?

327
00:18:09,233 --> 00:18:11,133
Is she awake?

328
00:18:11,300 --> 00:18:12,933
She couldn't sleep, Jade.

329
00:18:13,033 --> 00:18:16,300
What? She had her eyes closed
before I left.

330
00:18:16,467 --> 00:18:18,000
But she still
couldn't sleep.

331
00:18:20,533 --> 00:18:23,300
Luna shouldn't be left alone.

332
00:18:23,433 --> 00:18:26,000
What happened to her
wasn't easy.

333
00:18:26,100 --> 00:18:27,500
Okay, Leon.

334
00:18:27,600 --> 00:18:29,700
I'll make sure she always
has someone with her.

335
00:18:29,867 --> 00:18:30,967
Sir.

336
00:18:32,367 --> 00:18:33,467
Edward?

337
00:18:33,567 --> 00:18:40,533
[UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

338
00:18:43,700 --> 00:18:45,000
I've got this.

339
00:18:47,000 --> 00:18:49,533
I'll call Dr. Javier
to check on Luna.

340
00:18:49,700 --> 00:18:56,667
[UNEASY MUSIC CONTINUES]

341
00:18:59,800 --> 00:19:03,233
A dead guest was found on
the Hotel 88 property.

342
00:19:05,300 --> 00:19:07,000
Do you know who it is?

343
00:19:08,433 --> 00:19:10,367
Peter Montevilla.

344
00:19:10,533 --> 00:19:12,100
Connected to the Almazans.

345
00:19:13,233 --> 00:19:15,200
Luna Almazan's ex.

346
00:19:16,767 --> 00:19:18,067
Good.

347
00:19:19,800 --> 00:19:22,033
Make it their biggest
problem now

348
00:19:22,133 --> 00:19:25,033
to cover up
the issues I have.

349
00:19:25,200 --> 00:19:27,700
And when things get worse
at Hotel 88,

350
00:19:28,800 --> 00:19:30,733
they'll be forced to take
me on as a partner.

351
00:19:30,900 --> 00:19:36,133
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

352
00:19:40,733 --> 00:19:41,967
What are you doing here?

353
00:19:44,967 --> 00:19:46,567
I heard what happened.

354
00:19:48,100 --> 00:19:49,900
Luna knows him, right?

355
00:19:54,133 --> 00:19:55,133
How is she?

356
00:19:58,967 --> 00:20:00,567
She's still in shock.

357
00:20:01,433 --> 00:20:02,533
But...

358
00:20:02,800 --> 00:20:05,300
we're giving her time
to process things.

359
00:20:07,033 --> 00:20:09,500
Um, would you like anything?

360
00:20:09,667 --> 00:20:11,500
- Coffee, water, juice?
- No, no, no, Jade.

361
00:20:11,633 --> 00:20:12,900
- Anything?
- I'm good.

362
00:20:13,700 --> 00:20:14,667
Thank you.

363
00:20:15,300 --> 00:20:16,433
[JADE] Let's go over there.

364
00:20:16,933 --> 00:20:19,100
Okay, let's go.

365
00:20:21,933 --> 00:20:23,167
[EDWARD EXHALES DEEPLY]

366
00:20:26,367 --> 00:20:27,400
How are you?

367
00:20:30,000 --> 00:20:31,900
You're the one
who found Peter, right?

368
00:20:33,200 --> 00:20:38,667
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

369
00:20:38,833 --> 00:20:40,267
I'm fine.

370
00:20:41,233 --> 00:20:43,200
Well, I don't know
if me running there

371
00:20:43,333 --> 00:20:46,100
was a good thing or a bad thing.

372
00:20:47,833 --> 00:20:50,867
But, you know, it was a good
thing Kiko was following me.

373
00:20:51,033 --> 00:20:53,700
At least I wasn't alone.

374
00:20:56,667 --> 00:21:00,033
Anyway, that's not important.

375
00:21:01,233 --> 00:21:04,667
What matters now
is my sister.

376
00:21:04,800 --> 00:21:11,267
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

377
00:21:32,933 --> 00:21:39,733
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

378
00:21:41,033 --> 00:21:43,033
[SOBS, SNIFFLES]

379
00:21:48,100 --> 00:21:49,433
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

380
00:21:52,700 --> 00:21:54,100
Sir, this is Peter.

381
00:21:55,433 --> 00:21:56,567
You bastard.

382
00:21:57,933 --> 00:21:59,600
How are you going
to pay me now?

383
00:22:00,633 --> 00:22:02,100
I have so much debt, dude.

384
00:22:02,267 --> 00:22:03,667
I owe a lot of money at home.

385
00:22:03,800 --> 00:22:05,267
I've got to pay for it, dude!

386
00:22:05,433 --> 00:22:08,433
We'll need the contact details
of his relatives

387
00:22:09,067 --> 00:22:10,700
so we can tell them
what happened to him.

388
00:22:12,200 --> 00:22:14,167
I don't have
his parents' numbers.

389
00:22:16,000 --> 00:22:17,800
But I do know where he lived.

390
00:22:20,300 --> 00:22:22,633
We all know that Montevilla
had a lot of enemies.

391
00:22:23,167 --> 00:22:24,767
But what do you think?

392
00:22:28,067 --> 00:22:29,967
[CHASE] Which of them
would do this to him?

393
00:22:30,133 --> 00:22:35,033
[GRIM MUSIC CONTINUES]

394
00:22:35,167 --> 00:22:36,267
It's simple.

395
00:22:36,967 --> 00:22:39,033
Whoever he last fought with.

396
00:22:40,267 --> 00:22:43,467
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

397
00:22:43,633 --> 00:22:44,633
The Almazans.

398
00:22:52,500 --> 00:22:54,333
Sir, is it your hobby
to arrest me?

399
00:22:54,767 --> 00:22:55,933
This is not a good joke.

400
00:22:56,033 --> 00:22:58,400
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

401
00:22:58,533 --> 00:23:00,167
What have you done, Justin?

402
00:23:01,200 --> 00:23:03,733
That's the first thing you ask?!
Whether I did something?!

403
00:23:04,533 --> 00:23:07,567
[HENRI] We want to invite Justin
and Luna to the station.

404
00:23:07,967 --> 00:23:10,100
It's about the death of
Mr. Peter Montevilla.

405
00:23:10,200 --> 00:23:11,500
- What?
- No.

406
00:23:11,667 --> 00:23:13,300
My brother
had nothing to do with it.

407
00:23:13,433 --> 00:23:14,400
Why me?

408
00:23:14,567 --> 00:23:16,267
[JUSTIN] I wasn't even there
when his body was found.

409
00:23:17,367 --> 00:23:19,100
You've talked to Luna.

410
00:23:19,600 --> 00:23:21,233
What else do you
need from my brother?

411
00:23:21,400 --> 00:23:22,633
[HENRI] We have obtained
some information

412
00:23:22,733 --> 00:23:25,200
about their connection
with Mr. Montevilla.

413
00:23:26,633 --> 00:23:28,433
You know they can refuse,
right?

414
00:23:30,067 --> 00:23:31,367
[HENRI] I know.

415
00:23:31,800 --> 00:23:33,533
But if they really have
nothing to do with it,

416
00:23:34,200 --> 00:23:36,467
they can answer my questions
freely.

417
00:23:38,967 --> 00:23:40,200
[LUNA] I'll go.

418
00:23:40,367 --> 00:23:43,467
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

419
00:23:43,567 --> 00:23:45,533
Whatever you want to ask,
I can answer them.

420
00:23:45,700 --> 00:23:46,667
I'm not hiding anything.

421
00:23:50,533 --> 00:23:51,467
Fine.

422
00:23:52,067 --> 00:23:53,200
I'll go too.

423
00:23:59,533 --> 00:24:01,200
<i> He went to the hotel.</i>

424
00:24:01,333 --> 00:24:03,167
<i>He's the one who did
something wrong to me.</i>

425
00:24:03,267 --> 00:24:04,733
<i> That's why you retaliated.</i>

426
00:24:04,867 --> 00:24:05,500
<i> What?</i>

427
00:24:05,800 --> 00:24:08,367
<i>That man's death
has something to do</i>

428
00:24:08,500 --> 00:24:11,233
<i>with the hidden secrets
of Hotel 88.</i>

429
00:24:11,400 --> 00:24:13,033
<i>Why do you want
to help us?</i>

430
00:24:13,167 --> 00:24:14,367
<i> Why Hotel 88?</i>

431
00:24:14,500 --> 00:24:16,133
<i>Because it has something
I want.</i>

432
00:24:17,500 --> 00:24:19,400
<i>There's treasure
here in Hotel 88.</i>

433
00:24:19,567 --> 00:24:20,500
<i> Treasure?</i>

434
00:24:21,767 --> 00:24:23,067
<i> It's not just a book.</i>

435
00:24:23,200 --> 00:24:24,733
<i>We have to be careful
from now on.</i>

436
00:24:24,867 --> 00:24:25,567
<i> All of us.</i>

437
00:24:25,767 --> 00:24:27,133
<i>- What are you doing here?
- Leon!</i>

438
00:24:27,267 --> 00:24:28,633
<i>- Leave us alone!
- What?</i>

439
00:24:28,800 --> 00:24:30,167
<i> Leave my family alone!</i>

440
00:24:30,300 --> 00:24:31,433
<i> Leon, what's wrong with you?</i>

441
00:24:31,600 --> 00:24:34,400
<i>They say fish get caught
by the mouth.</i>

442
00:24:34,533 --> 00:24:38,033
<i>To me, they get caught
when they don't know</i>

443
00:24:38,133 --> 00:24:39,567
<i> someone's out to catch them.</i>

444
00:24:39,967 --> 00:24:40,867
<i> Syvera.</i>

445
00:24:40,967 --> 00:24:41,867
<i> The trunk.</i>
